SIMPLE: competitor
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Competitor
<hw>Com*pet"i*tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.: cf. F.
<ets>comp⟦eacute⟧titeur</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who seeks
what another seeks, or claims what another claims; one who competes; a
rival.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And can not brook <qex>competitors</qex> in love.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An associate; a confederate.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Every hour more <qex>competitors</qex>⟦br⟧
Flock to their aid, and still their power increaseth.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Competitory</ent>⟦br⟧
